<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="597" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1655,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,632,1834,1861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
Description. Male (
<figureCitation box="[427,528,1834,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1031,1055]" captionTargetBox="[186,1400,179,1005]" captionTargetId="figure-19@1.[186,1400,179,1005]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus (alive) of P. luojishanensis sp. nov. and T. nigripes sp. nov. A. P. luojishanensisi, female; B. P. luojishanensis, male; C. T. nigripes, female; D. T. nigripes, male. Photographed by He, Zhixin." pageId="1" pageNumber="594">Figs. 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[540,576,1835,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1369,1393]" captionTargetBox="[250,1354,179,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[232,1354,179,1344]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of T. nigripes sp. nov. A. Male; B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="594">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[589,624,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,188,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[189,1398,179,1653]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Photographs of Trigonidium nigripes sp. nov. A. lateral view of male; B. lateral view of female; C. male tegmen; D. female tegmen; E. dorsal view of head; F. ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="594">4A</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
Body medium-sized for the genus. Except distal portion of the fore and mesofemora and the base of the hind tibia dark brown, the remaining parts of the crickets are black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1655,2041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1906,1933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[280,371,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,188,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[189,1398,179,1653]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Photographs of Trigonidium nigripes sp. nov. A. lateral view of male; B. lateral view of female; C. male tegmen; D. female tegmen; E. dorsal view of head; F. ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." pageId="1" pageNumber="594">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Vertex and genae armed with long setae. Compound eyes large, laterally protruding; ocelli present, with compound eyes linked by two light stripes, lateral ocelli absent. Antennal scape cylindrical, narrower than frontal costa; flagellum slender with small villi. Maxillary palpi with the apical segment apically transverse and broad; labial palpi relatively short.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,982,1369,1394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" startId="2.[151,250,1369,1393]" targetBox="[250,1354,179,1329]" targetPageId="2">
