</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[666,747,1679,1703]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[666,747,1679,1703]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. lateral view of male; B. lateral view of female; C. male tegmen; D. female tegmen; E. dorsal view of head; F. ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1785,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,1785,1811]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[333,465,1785,1811]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,188,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[189,1398,179,1653]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Photographs of Trigonidium nigripes sp. nov. A. lateral view of male; B. lateral view of female; C. male tegmen; D. female tegmen; E. dorsal view of head; F. ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="596">Figs. 4C, D</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. Pronotum covered with fine setae, disc sparsely with long setae; anterior and posterior margin with long setae. Tegmen almost extending to abdominal apex; dorsal field with six elevated longitudinal veins and false veins; transverse veins between longitudinal veins inconspicuous; hindwings absent. Fore femur and fore tibia with short fine hairs; fore tibia with tympanum absent, only a single apical spur; middle tibia with a single apical spur; hind femur dark color, middle tibia with three pairs of dorsal spurs and five apical spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1785,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,1965,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="596">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[323,488,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2018,2042]" captionTargetBox="[223,1359,1418,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-46@2.[222,1364,1416,1992]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia of T. nigripes sp. nov. A. Dorsal view; B. Lateral view; C. Ventral view. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="596">Figs. 3A, B, C</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
. In dorsal view, epiphallus broadened, lateral lobe of epiphallus round, tapering with denticulations, curved inward; Ectoparamere short and bifurcated, upper branch hook-like and curved inward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,392]" box="[199,1121,150,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">
Female (
<figureCitation box="[301,401,150,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1031,1055]" captionTargetBox="[186,1400,179,1005]" captionTargetId="figure-19@1.[186,1400,179,1005]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus (alive) of P. luojishanensis sp. nov. and T. nigripes sp. nov. A. P. luojishanensisi, female; B. P. luojishanensis, male; C. T. nigripes, female; D. T. nigripes, male. Photographed by He, Zhixin." pageId="4" pageNumber="597">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
, 
