<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="597" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,258,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">Remarks</emphasis>
. This new species is distinguished from other members of the genus by the following: black legs, the others are usually light colored. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yuan &amp; Zheng &amp; Ma &amp; Gu, 2022" authorityName="Yuan &amp; Zheng &amp; Ma &amp; Gu" authorityYear="2022" box="[515,637,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[515,531,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[545,637,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[644,734,294,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[644,734,294,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Rambur, 1838" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1838" box="[882,1343,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cicindeloides">
<emphasis box="[882,1177,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">Trigonidium cicindeloides</emphasis>
Rambur, 
<quantity box="[1287,1343,294,320]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66852" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" unit="in" value="1838.0">1838</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in ectoparamere (both of them bifurcate), but the upper branch of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yuan &amp; Zheng &amp; Ma &amp; Gu, 2022" authorityName="Yuan &amp; Zheng &amp; Ma &amp; Gu" authorityYear="2022" box="[807,926,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Trigonidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[807,926,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">T. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[932,1021,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[932,1021,330,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="597" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is longer and more curved; the lower branch is blunt and rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
